From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Patric Stout <github@truebrain.nl>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 21:40:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 12/13] fix(tests): clear pending exception in PyTasklet_Insert
 test

The test asserted that PyTasklet_Insert on a dead tasklet returns -1 (which
sets a RuntimeError) but never called PyErr_Clear(), leaving a Python
exception set for the rest of the process's lifetime. This tripped the
CPython internal assertion '_PyType_Lookup: Assertion !PyErr_Occurred()
failed' during later type lookups in the same interpreter.
---
 tests/capiTest/Tasklet.cpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tests/capiTest/Tasklet.cpp b/tests/capiTest/Tasklet.cpp
index 71f3013..40dfe80 100644
--- a/tests/capiTest/Tasklet.cpp
+++ b/tests/capiTest/Tasklet.cpp
@@ -194,6 +194,8 @@ TEST_F( TaskletCapi, PyTasklet_Insert )
 	EXPECT_EQ( m_api->PyTasklet_Alive( reinterpret_cast<PyTaskletObject*>( tasklet ) ), 0 );
 
     EXPECT_EQ( m_api->PyTasklet_Insert( reinterpret_cast<PyTaskletObject*>( tasklet ) ), -1 );
+    EXPECT_NE( PyErr_Occurred(), nullptr );
+    PyErr_Clear();
 
     // Clean
 	Py_XDECREF( tasklet );
